6. Saga resumes
The card never resumes the saga directly.
Only events do.
Adaptive Cards inside Saga-Based Architectures
In event-driven systems, this becomes even more powerful.
Approval-Gated Saga
A saga is a long-running business transaction with multiple steps.
Adaptive Cards allow a saga to pause safely.
Saga Step
↓
Policy Check
↓
Needs Approval?
├─ No → Continue
└─ Yes
↓
WAITING_FOR_APPROVAL
↓
Adaptive Card (Teams)
↓
Human Decision
↓ ↓
Approve Reject
↓ ↓
Continue Compensate
This is critical for:
- Finance approvals
- Legal exceptions
- HR changes
- Compliance-sensitive operations
The saga remains deterministic, auditable, and recoverable.
Example: Finance Approval Architecture
Scenario
High-value invoice payment requires finance approval.
Flow
- Payment saga reaches “Release Payment”
- Policy detects amount threshold breach
- Saga pauses
- Finance approver receives Adaptive Card
- Approval resumes payment
- Rejection triggers compensation
No emails.
No portals.
No ambiguity.
